Just to answer your question vliegtuig, the reason "Crablouse" isn't on the soundtrack is because it was used for the trailer, not the actual film - Snyder actually has no part in the trailer cuts, they're made by a separate company that specializes in the cutting and distribution of movie trailers, so it's not officially part of the Sucker Punch soundtrack. This is the same reason that "Panic Switch" by Silversun Pickups isn't on the soundtrack either (which is also an awesome song!).

Those other songs you mentioned are what's called the "score" of the movie... and this what Wikipedia lists as those songs:

Tyler Bates (who composed all of Snyder's previous live-action films) and Marius de Vries (who composed the score for the film Moulin Rouge!) wrote the score for Sucker Punch. The official trailers contain samples from the songs "Prologue" by Immediate Music, "Crablouse" by Lords of Acid, "When the Levee Breaks" by Led Zeppelin, "Tomorrow Never Knows" by The Beatles, "And Your World Will Burn" by Cliff Lin, and "Panic Switch" by the Silversun Pickups.
They'll probably be released soon as an official score of the film.
